parameters.name: ClientToken
parameters.description:
The client token that is used to ensure the idempotence of the request. You can use the client to generate the value, but you must make sure that it is unique among different requests.

The token can only contain ASCII characters and cannot exceed 64 characters in length.

parameters.name: DBInstanceId
parameters.description: The instance ID. You can call the DescribeDBInstances operation to query the ID of the instance.

parameters.name: ResourceGroupId
parameters.description: The ID of the resource group. You can call the DescribeDBInstanceAttribute operation to obtain the ID of the resource group.
